author: akarasulu
msg: Changed it so responses no longer take the request as a constructor arg
and do not return the request with a getRequest accessor method.  There
is no way to accommodate the various ways in which Response objects are
created an provide the request as an argument to a response constructor
so we have abandoned the notion of coupling the two.  External means
can be used to associate the requests and responses of a session by the
message id value - such functionality is out of the scope of this API.
